## Conditional Caching

### Environment-Based

```ruby
# Only cache in production
def index
  if Rails.env.production?
    @articles = Rails.cache.fetch('published_articles', expires_in: 10.minutes) do
      Article.published.recent.limit(20).to_a
    end
  else
    @articles = Article.published.recent.limit(20)
  end
end
```

### User-Based

```ruby
def show
  # Don't cache for article author (always show fresh data)
  if @article.user == Current.user
    @article_data = fetch_article_data(@article)
  else
    @article_data = Rails.cache.fetch(['article', @article.id, 'data'], expires_in: 5.minutes) do
      fetch_article_data(@article)
    end
  end
end
```

